Spring Boot + MyBatis (SSM) REST API project.

## Tech Stack
- Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2.5, MyBatis 3.0.3
- MySQL 8.0, Maven

## Quick Start (Docker)
```bash
docker compose up --build
```
App runs at http://<HOST>:8080. MySQL starts automatically with schema initialized.

## Manual Setup
1. Install Java 17+ and Maven 3.9+
2. Start MySQL and create database: `source sql/schema.sql`
3. Run: `mvn spring-boot:run`

## API Endpoints
| Method | URL | Description |
|--------|-----|-------------|
| GET | /api/users | List all users |
| GET | /api/users/:id | Get user by ID |
| POST | /api/users | Create user |
| PUT | /api/users/:id | Update user |
| DELETE | /api/users/:id | Delete user |

## Testing
```bash
chmod +x run_tests.sh && ./run_tests.sh
```

## Project Structure
```
src/main/java/com/example/
  controller/   — REST endpoints
  service/      — Business logic
  mapper/       — MyBatis data access
  entity/       — Data models
  config/       — Configuration
sql/            — Database schema
unit_tests/     — Unit tests
API_tests/      — API integration tests
```"}]

